        "featureSummary": {
          "description": "AIS Webhook Token is a bearer token used to authorise incoming AIS webhook requests before the site accepts the data they send.",
          "notes": [
            "Incoming webhook calls must send the token as a bearer token. The request is rejected unless the token is active and belongs to the current environment.",
